By Andile Mngxitama On 25 May 2020, I went live on my Facebook page and engaged on the colonial border question. The question of whether to open (as suggested by Julius Malema) or to close (as argued by Herman Mashaba) the borders, entails  two sides of the same white monopoly capital (WMC) coin. Malema says “open the borders!” He then run into Adriano Mazzotti’s compound. This is the Pan Afrikanism of smugglers. It is a fake solution. It’s not about one Africa. It’s about the imperialist and local white monopoly capital (WMC) handlers and benefactors. There is also the fake solution of “close the borders”. “Open the borders” or “close the borders“, what’s to be done? Watch the full presentation: https://www.facebook.com/andile.mngxi/videos/1683171781841663/ Andile Mngxitama is the President of Black First Land First (BLF), a radical black consciousness organization.